title: Volume of manifolds

The //volume// of a [[smooth manifold|Smooth manifold]] $$M$$ with a specified [[volume form|Volume form]] $$\varOmega$$ is defined to be 

$$
\vol(M)\coloneqq \int_M 1 \,\d\vol = \int_M \varOmega.
$$

If $$M$$ is compact, this works directly. If it is not, take the limit over a compact exhaustion.